World War II was fought from 1939 to 1945. The war began on September 1, 1939, when Nazi Germany invaded Poland, and it lasted until September 2, 1945, when Japan formally surrendered, following the atomic bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki by the United States. The war involved many countries around the world and was one of the deadliest conflicts in human history, resulting in the deaths of millions of people, including civilians and military personnel.